Output shape — Pattern A scene fragment, ONE `<div>` written to the
compositions file for the chosen scene_id:

```html
<div id="scene-<scene_id>" class="scene clip"
     data-start="<scene_start>" data-duration="<scene_duration>" data-track-index="{{ data_track_index }}"
     data-width="{{ data_width }}" data-height="{{ data_height }}">
  <style>
    /* EVERY rule prefixed with #scene-<scene_id> — no bare class selectors. */
    #scene-<scene_id> { position: absolute; inset: 0; <opacity-init>; }
    /* …per-element rules… */
  </style>
  <div class="scene-content">
    <!-- ≥ 8 elements visible at hero frame; ≥ 2 BG decoratives with ambient motion -->
  </div>
  <script>
    (function() {
      window.__sceneTimelines = window.__sceneTimelines || {};
      const tl = gsap.timeline({ paused: true });
      // entrance-only, every entrance via tl.fromTo()
      // ≥ 3 distinct eases; first entrance offset 0.1–0.3s
      window.__sceneTimelines["<scene_id>"] = tl;
    })();
  </script>
</div>
```

Substitute:
- `<scene_id>` → the scene_id you picked.
- `<scene_start>` and `<scene_duration>` → the values from the parallel
  arrays above for that scene's index.
- `<opacity-init>` → `opacity: 1` for the FIRST scene in plan order (index 0),
  `opacity: 0` for any other scene (the visibility shim sets opacity at start).

Hard rules (orchestrator-house — derived from canon, surfaced so you don't miss them):
- **`class="scene clip"` on the scene div** — `clip` is required by HF lint.
- **CSS scoping** — every rule prefixed with `#scene-<scene_id>`. No bare class selectors.
- **`tl.fromTo()` only** for entrances — never `tl.from()`, never bare `gsap.from()`.
- **No `data-composition-id` on the scene div.**
- **No `<template>` wrapper.**
- **No `<script src=".../gsap...">`** — root scaffold supplies GSAP once.
- **IIFE-wrap the entire script body** — un-IIFE'd `const tl` collides with
  the scaffold's top-level `const tl` and trips `hyperframes validate` with
  `Identifier 'tl' has already been declared`.
- **Density floor**: ≥ 8 elements visible at the hero frame, ≥ 2 BG
  decoratives with ambient motion (`tl.to()` on the seekable `tl`).
- **≥ 3 distinct eases**; first entrance offset 0.1–0.3s.
- **Final-fade (HR 4)**: permitted ONLY on the last scene (highest index in
  plan order). Otherwise NO `tl.to(..., {opacity: 0})` on the scene container.
- **NO infinite repeats** — the GSAP infinite-repeat sentinel is forbidden
  (canon: SKILL.md §"Animation Guardrails" L227 + Rules L240). Compute
  finite counts from `data-duration` and tween duration. Never write the
  literal token `repeat:` followed by the infinite sentinel even inside
  comments — HF lint regex false-positives on the substring.

